profile_positions.description:
Founded in 1913, it is currently one the biggest universities of the Netherlands with a student population of 23,000 and a research community of circa 1,400. Scholars and students in seven faculties and two institutions work on global social challenges in the areas of:
•health, wealth, governance and culture.

Activities:
-Secure and improve structured and professional testing within the Erasmus University;
-Specify procedures, standards and norms in the field of testing;
-Form , supervise and assess test teams for projects and releases;
-Maintain contacts inside and outside of IT departments at both operational and management level;
-Support and coaching of Erasmus University colleagues in the field of testing;
-Establish and monitor testing process risks;
-Take care of the approval to application management.
-Implement Test management tool Tosca
